sec.p:
Expression data for genes of interest were extracted from the RNA assay slot of the Seurat object using GetAssayData(). Cells were classified as expressing a gene if their count was greater than zero. The number of cells expressing each gene individually and both genes concurrently was computed. The percentage of Gene1-expressing cells that also expressed Gene2 was calculated as:Percent Co-Expression=(Cells expressing both genesTotal cells expressing Gene1)×100Percent Co-Expression=(Cells expressing both genesTotal cells expressing Gene1)×100Percent Co-Expression=(Total cells expressing Gene1Cells expressing both genes)×100 egin{document}$$\displaystyle  egin{align} &	ext{Percent Co-Expression} 
onumber\ &=(	ext{Cells expressing both genesTotal cells expressing Gene1}) 
onumber	imes 100 \ &	ext{Percent Co-Expression} 
onumber\ &=\left(  rac{	ext{Cells expressing both genes}} {	ext{Total cells expressing Gene1}} ight) 	imes 100 
onumber\ &	ext{Percent Co-Expression} 
onumber\ &=(	ext{Total cells expressing Gene1Cells expressing both genes}) 	imes 100 
onumber\end{align} $$\end{document}
